<br>
there's a problem with that. For instance. A couple of very good points were raised in our private msg boards.<br>
<br>
1. e.g 2 wizards see a excellent wiz item drop. They cohort and decide that one will take it now and the other later. Nooone bids for it. We revert to a bid system. They both get away with buying the item (the second one on a later date) for nearly zero and the system fails<br>
<br>
2. Both wizard want the item, the one with highest points wins, second time around the second wizard doesnt declare he wants it, we fall back to a bid system, he's the only one there , he gets it for nearly free. The system fails.<br>
<br>
i can make numerous such examples. <br>
<br>
That's why we're still sticking with the current system.<br>
<br>
