<br>
How about you have two rounds: one round would be for mains, and the second round would be for twinks/friends. If no ones main wants to invest the points in an item that is nonmqable and no drop, then open up the item as a percentage off or biddable up to the amount of the item to everyones twink or for their friend's gf's account <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . For example, my GF plays a 45th level monk. Let's say no monk wants a good monk item, but there are some people in the guild who have monk twinks that would love the item. Open up the item to them for either points or for bids. This way, mains cannot conspire to trick the point system, but an item also doesn't have to rot.<br>
